OL,3,CMinister makes emotional pilgrimage to
OL,4,CJapan to honour POW father
OL,6,FA minister has fulfilled a 60-year
OL,7,Fdream to make a pilgrimage to Japan in
OL,8,Fhonour of his late father who was kept
OL,9,Fprisoner there during the Second World
OL,10,FWar.
OL,12,FRev Ian Gilmour, a retired Church of
OL,13,FScotland minister from Edinburgh,
OL,14,Ftravelled to Hiroshima where Private
OL,15,FDavid Gilmour was held in a work camp
OL,16,Ffor more than three years.
OL,18,FThe camp was liberated after the
OL,19,FAmerican B-29 bomber Enola Gay dropped
OL,20,Fan atomic bomb over the city on August
OL,21,F6, 1945.
