OL,3,CMinister makes emotional pilgrimage to
OL,4,CJapan to honour POW father
OL,6,FPrivate Gilmour, of the Royal Army
OL,7,FService Corps, was captured by the
OL,8,FJapanese during the Battle of
OL,9,FSingapore in February 1942.
OL,11,FHe was badly mistreated when he
OL,12,Fimprisoned, forced to work on a
OL,13,Fminuscule diet of poor-quality rice
OL,14,Fand suffered from Beriberi disease and
OL,15,Fdysentery due to malnutrition.
OL,17,FPrivate Gilmour was in and out of
OL,18,Fhospital during his captivity and only
OL,19,Fweighed six stone when he was finally
OL,20,Fset free on August 15 1945.
