OL,3,CMinister makes emotional pilgrimage to
OL,4,CJapan to honour POW father
OL,6,FHe was unable to find the exact
OL,7,Flocation of the camp as it is not a
OL,8,Fplace the Japanese choose to remember,
OL,9,Fso he instead visited the Hiroshima
OL,10,FPeace Memorial.
OL,12,FHe placed his father's British Army
OL,13,Ffield book on an altar surrounded by
OL,14,Fflowers and prayed for peace during
OL,15,Fhis stay.
OL,17,F"It was very moving and I feel that I
OL,18,Fhonoured my father's memory ` it felt
OL,19,Fgood and right and it meant a lot to
OL,20,Fme," he said.
