OL,6,F"It was important for me to take his
OL,7,Farmy field book so that there was
OL,8,Fsomething owned by him going back to
OL,9,FJapan.
OL,11,F"It was an upsetting experience as I
OL,12,Freflected on what happened to him, his
OL,13,Ffellow prisoners of war and the tens
OL,14,Fof thousands of civilians who died
OL,15,Fafter the bomb was dropped.
OL,17,F"It was emotional as it allowed me to
OL,18,Fbetter value his life and what he went
OL,19,Fthrough and acknowledge that my life
OL,20,Fand my family's life came out of
OL,21,Fterrible suffering.
